
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  MISSION: SIGNAL PARSING                                                  ║
║  SKILL: cut, awk, field extraction                                        ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
The signal log contains structured data about all received transmissions.
Extract specific fields to analyze the data and find the priority message.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Find the Priority Code
────────────────────────────
The file 'transmission_log.csv' contains structured data with fields:

    TIMESTAMP,SOURCE,PRIORITY,SIGNAL_STRENGTH,MESSAGE_ID

Find the MESSAGE_ID of the transmission with:
- SOURCE = "EARTH"
- PRIORITY = "CRITICAL"

There should be only one CRITICAL priority message from EARTH.
Extract its MESSAGE_ID.

When you find it, run:
    ./verify <message_id>

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

USEFUL COMMANDS:
    cat transmission_log.csv | head -5         See structure
    cut -d',' -f2 file                         Get SOURCE field (2nd)
    cut -d',' -f3 file                         Get PRIORITY field (3rd)
    cut -d',' -f5 file                         Get MESSAGE_ID (5th)

    grep "EARTH" file | grep "CRITICAL"        Two-stage filter
    grep "EARTH.*CRITICAL" file                Pattern matching

    awk -F',' '{print $5}' file                Print 5th field
    awk -F',' '$2=="EARTH" {print $0}' file    Filter by field value

PIPELINE:
    grep "EARTH" file | grep "CRITICAL" | cut -d',' -f5

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

